Metadata-Version: 1.2
Name: icolor
Version: 1.2
Summary: Interpolate ANSI colors in strings
Home-page: https://github.com/brianmhunt/icolor
Author: Brian Hunt
Author-email: brianmhunt@gmail.com
License: MIT
Description: Change codes from readable codes e.g. #RED; to ANSI escape codes.

    Here is an example:

        cformat("This is #RED;a red string.")

        cprint("This #BLUE;string#RESET; has #GREEN;Two#BOLD;Colors")


    ANSI Properties
    ===============
    
      Foreground colors:
    
        BLACK, RED, GREEN, YELLOW, BLUE, MAGENTA, CYAN, WHITE, DEFAULT

      Background colors:

        BLACKBG, REDBG, ..., DEFAULTBG

    
      Attributes:
    
        RESET, BOLD, INVERSE, STRIKE, UNBOLD

Platform: UNKNOWN
